	<article data-post-id="167720" class="tag-ag-burning tag-agricultural-burning tag-agricultural-waste tag-agriculture tag-air-pollution tag-air-quality tag-air-quality-index tag-air-resources-board tag-almond-farms tag-arvin tag-asthma tag-burning-agriculture tag-california-air-quality tag-california-air-resources-board tag-california-governor tag-central-valley-air-quality-coalition tag-childhood-asthma tag-communities-of-color tag-drought tag-easton tag-environmental-justice tag-fresno tag-fresno-county tag-gavin-newsom tag-health-care tag-kern-county tag-lebec tag-lodi tag-low-income-communities tag-mary-nichols tag-n95 tag-n95-respirators tag-orchards tag-san-joaquin-valley tag-san-joaquin-valley-air-pollution-control-district tag-vineyard-burns tag-vineyards category-environment type-post post-has-image amp-wp-e70b344" data-amp-original-style="min-height: 0vh; padding-top: 0vh;">
					<figure class="post-thumbnail">
								<a href="https://calmatters.org/environment/2021/02/san-joaquin-valley-agriculture-burns/" rel="bookmark">
									<amp-img width="1200" height="900" src="https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=1200%2C900&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-newspack-article-block-landscape-large size-newspack-article-block-landscape-large wp-post-image amp-wp-enforced-sizes i-amphtml-layout-intrinsic i-amphtml-layout-size-defined" alt="Laura Garcia stands outside her family home in the rural Fresno County community of Raisin City on Feb. 12, 2021. Garcia, a mother of 5 with one on the way, is concerned about how the air quality due to nearby burns is affecting her kids. The orchard in the background replaced a vineyard which was burned away. Photo by Craig Kohlruss, The Fresno Bee" object-fit="cover" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=1200%2C900&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=800%2C600&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=400%2C300&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=200%2C150&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" layout="intrinsic" disable-inline-width="" i-amphtml-layout="intrinsic"><i-amphtml-sizer class="i-amphtml-sizer"><img alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="i-amphtml-intrinsic-sizer" role="presentation" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyBoZWlnaHQ9JzkwMCcgd2lkdGg9JzEyMDAnIHhtbG5zPSdodHRwOi8vd3d3LnczLm9yZy8yMDAwL3N2ZycgdmVyc2lvbj0nMS4xJy8+"></i-amphtml-sizer><noscript><img width="1200" height="900" src="https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=1200%2C900&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-newspack-article-block-landscape-large size-newspack-article-block-landscape-large wp-post-image" alt="Laura Garcia stands outside her family home in the rural Fresno County community of Raisin City on Feb. 12, 2021. Garcia, a mother of 5 with one on the way, is concerned about how the air quality due to nearby burns is affecting her kids. The orchard in the background replaced a vineyard which was burned away. Photo by Craig Kohlruss, The Fresno Bee" loading="lazy" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=1200%2C900&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=800%2C600&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=400%2C300&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i2.wp.com/calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/FresnoBee_AgBurns_01.jpg?resize=200%2C150&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px"></noscript></amp-img>								</a>
				
							</figure><!-- .featured-image -->
		
		<div class="entry-wrapper">
			<h3 class="entry-title"><a href="https://calmatters.org/environment/2021/02/san-joaquin-valley-agriculture-burns/" rel="bookmark">Up in smoke: Burns in San Joaquin Valley vineyards, orchards may finally end</a></h3>						<p>California’s air board will vote this week on stopping burns that spew plumes of smoke that can trigger asthma attacks. The move is long in coming — it was supposed to end a decade ago under state law. </p>
				<div class="entry-meta">
					<a href="https://calmatters.org/author/rachel-becker/"><amp-img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fb44a1795793cc57f4632d6abf93ccfe?s=48&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fb44a1795793cc57f4632d6abf93ccfe?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-48 photo amp-wp-enforced-sizes i-amphtml-layout-intrinsic i-amphtml-layout-size-defined" height="48" width="48" layout="intrinsic" i-amphtml-layout="intrinsic"><i-amphtml-sizer class="i-amphtml-sizer"><img alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="i-amphtml-intrinsic-sizer" role="presentation" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyBoZWlnaHQ9JzQ4JyB3aWR0aD0nNDgnIHhtbG5zPSdodHRwOi8vd3d3LnczLm9yZy8yMDAwL3N2ZycgdmVyc2lvbj0nMS4xJy8+"></i-amphtml-sizer><noscript><img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fb44a1795793cc57f4632d6abf93ccfe?s=48&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fb44a1795793cc57f4632d6abf93ccfe?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-48 photo" height="48" width="48"></noscript></amp-img></a>							<span class="byline">
								<span class="author-prefix">by </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://calmatters.org/author/rachel-becker/">Rachel Becker</a></span>							</span><!-- .author-name -->
							<time class="entry-date published" datetime="2021-02-22T05:30:00-08:00">February 22, 2021</time><time class="updated" datetime="2021-02-22T15:21:51-08:00">February 22, 2021</time>				</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					</div><!-- .entry-wrapper -->
	</article>

		
	<article data-post-id="167096" class="tag-air-pollution tag-air-resources-board tag-california-air-resources-board tag-carbon-emissions tag-carbon-market tag-carbon-trading tag-climate-change tag-climate-crisis tag-climate-policy tag-environment tag-environmental-groups tag-environmental-justice tag-environmental-policy tag-environmental-protection tag-environmentalists tag-gavin-newsom tag-jared-blumenfeld tag-legislative-analyst tag-liane-randolph tag-mary-nichols tag-oil-and-gas tag-oil-industry tag-pollution category-environment type-post post-has-image amp-wp-e70b344" data-amp-original-style="min-height: 0vh; padding-top: 0vh;">
